      "orig": "5.2 Results We picked the model parameter configuration that produced the best quality (enc=6, dec=6, heads=8) with alone, then trained and evaluated it on three publicly available data sets: (395k samples), FinTabNet (113k samples) and (about 1M Performance results are presented in Table. 2. It is clearly evident that the model trained on OTSL outperforms HTML across the board, keeping high TEDs and mAP scores even on di ffi cult financial tables that contain sparse and large tables. the results show that OTSL has an over when applied on a bigger data set like and achieves improved scores. Finally, OTSL achieves faster inference due to fewer steps which is a result of the reduced sequence",
      "text": "5.2 Results We picked the model parameter configuration that produced the best quality (enc=6, dec=6, heads=8) with alone, then trained and evaluated it on three publicly available data sets: (395k samples), FinTabNet (113k samples) and (about 1M Performance results are presented in Table. 2. It is clearly evident that the model trained on OTSL outperforms HTML across the board, keeping high TEDs and mAP scores even on di ffi cult financial tables that contain sparse and large tables. the results show that OTSL has an over when applied on a bigger data set like and achieves improved scores. Finally, OTSL achieves faster inference due to fewer steps which is a result of the reduced sequence"
